# Project Overview

This project implements a GitHub repository loader using WebContainers, allowing users to load any GitHub repository into a browser-based sandbox and interact with it through a terminal interface.

## Key Features

- Browser-based Node.js runtime via WebContainers
- Load GitHub repositories directly in the browser
- Terminal interface to run commands against the loaded code
- Preview panel to view running applications
- Clean, minimal console-style UI

## Main Components

The main application structure:
- [index.html](mdc:test-web/index.html) - Main HTML entry point
- [src/main.js](mdc:test-web/src/main.js) - Core application logic and WebContainer implementation
- [src/style.css](mdc:test-web/src/style.css) - Styling for the console UI
- [loading.html](mdc:test-web/loading.html) - Loading screen for the iframe
- [vite.config.js](mdc:test-web/vite.config.js) - Vite configuration with necessary CORS headers
